title: Wilson's Tales of the Borders and of Scotland, Volume 18
author: Alexander Leighton
snippet: "They may gallop off with our horses," said Lag, in ajocular manner, by the way; "but they will not easily gallop off withthe old choked hound, who has led us so many dances over the hills ofQueensberry and Auchenleck."

title: Rambles in Europe:
author: Morrison, Leonard Allison
snippet: The road from Auchenleck to Glasgow is through a fine country filled with coal and iron works, whose huge chimneys belch forth, day after day and month after month, great columns of smoke, which blackens the atmosphere.

title: Rambles in Europe:
author: Morrison, Leonard Allison
snippet: ■ Going east fourteen miles to Auchenleck, I scanned the public record for 200 years, and found many familiar names, particularly the name of Cochran.
